sKeyword: NRTL 1. Introduction Organic esters are important intermediate products and products in pharmaceutical and chemical industries. Due to their strong solubility and miscibility with alcohol, ketone, ether and other solvents, n-propyl acetate (NPAC) and isopropyl acetate (IAC) are widely used in coatings, inks and other industries.1-3
Citation.sTitle: Liquid-Liquid Equilibrium Data for the Systems n-Propyl Acetate or Isopropyl Acetate + n-Propanol or Isopropyl Alcohol + IL at 298.15 and 318.15 K and Atmospheric Pressure
Citation.sAbstract: The liquid-liquid equilibrium data of the two ternary systems of n-propyl acetate + n-propanol + 1-Butyl-3-methylimidazolium hydrogensulfate and isopropyl acetate + isopropanol + 1-Butyl-3-methylimidazolium hydrogensulfate were measured at 298.15 K, 318.15 K and under atmospheric pressure in this work. The extraction effect of ionic liquids was discussed by comparing the values of distribution coefficient and separation factor. The influence of temperature on the liquid-liquid equilibrium data was discussed. The binary interaction parameters of NRTL and UNIQUAC models were obtained by regressing the experimental data.
